      "role": "user",
      "content": "so if they're used for \"geopolitical goals\" doesn't that mean they're basically more about politics than actual economics? like, if a country is losing money because of them but it helps their \"influence,\" isn't that just a bad trade policy? wouldn't a \"correct\" economist say they're always a net negative regardless of the politics?",
